    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-05T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-05T08:00:00-05:00" n="148"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9305</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-05T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 7, 11 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3874. Department’s 2117, June 18, 6 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d148fn1">“Can you
                        obtain copy German black list?”</note> Am informed that German black list no
                    longer exists, officially having been withdrawn by German Government about two
                    years ago. There is, however known to be a list of firms located in Switzerland
                    to which permits to forward merchandise through Germany to northern neutrals are
                    steadily refused by German Legation in Berne, but this list is strictly
                    confidential and it is doubtful if it could be obtained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
